    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-03T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-03T23:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-04T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 4 [<hi rend="italic">2?</hi>], 1947—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received
                        March 4—1:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>419. Government on March 1, midnight, announced the appointment of 50 new members
                    to the Legislative Yuan of whom 17 are Kuomintang, 13 Youth Party, 12 Social
                    Democrats and 8 non-partisan; 25 new members to Control Yuan of whom 9 are
                    Kuomintang, 6 Youth Party, 7 Social Democrats, and 3 non-partisan; and 44 new
                    members to the People’s Political Council of whom 11 are Kuomintang, 11 Youth
                    Party, 11 Social Democrats and 11 non-partisan. (ReEmbtel 390, February 28, 2
                    p.m.)</p>
                <p>Analysis will be made and submitted in due course.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
